#+title: smart contract

Smart contracts are user defined programs running on top of a blockchain. Suppose a domain name
registry in the Ethereum blockchain
#+begin_src javascript
  contract MyRegistry {
      // state saved on-chain
      mapping (string => address) public registry;
      
      // function in order to modify state
      function registerDomain(string memory domain) public {
          // ensure domain not already present
          require(registry[domain] == address(0));

          // add domain owner
          registry[domain] = msg.sender;
      }
  }
#+end_src

The =mapping= line is a storage line followed by a function (extrinsics)
